title: Fix SOT-363 parameters and add test snapshots for KiCad parity
description: Updates the SOT-363 footprint parameters and adds a test for visual parity with KiCads footprint using automated SVG comparisons.
body: This pull request updates the SOT-363 footprint parameters and adds a new test to check for parity with KiCad's footprint. The main focus is to improve the accuracy of the footprint and ensure visual consistency with KiCad using automated SVG comparisons. Footprint parameter updates: * Updated the `w` parameter from 1.94 to 2.56, `pw` from 0.3 to 0.4, and `pl` from 0.7 to 0.65 in the `sot363` footprint definition to better match the reference design. Testing and validation improvements: * Added a new test `sot363_kicad_parity.test.ts` that compares the generated SOT-363 footprint against KiCad's version using SVG snapshots and boolean difference analysis to ensure visual parity.

title: feat: Add support for inductors in subcircuit circuitJson
description: Adds support for inflating inductor components defined within a circuitJson property of a subcircuit.
body:
This change adds support for inflating inductor components when they are defined
within a circuitJson property of a subcircuit.                                  

This is achieved by:                                                            

 • Creating a new inflateSourceInductor function.                               
 • Integrating the new inflator into the Subcircuit component's inflation logic.
 • Adding a test case to validate the inflation of inductors from circuitJson.

title: feat: Add subcircuit circuitJson support for capacitors
description: Adds support for inflating capacitor components from circuitJson when used in a subcircuit
body:
This pull request introduces support for inflating capacitor components from    
circuitJson when used in a `<subcircuit>`.                                        

This is achieved by:                                                            

 • Adding inflateSourceCapacitor to create `<capacitor>` instances from           
   simple_capacitor elements in the circuitJson.                                
 • Integrating the new inflator into the Subcircuit component.                  
 • Adding a new test to verify that capacitors are correctly inflated from a    
   circuitJson definition.

title: Implement SOT363 with test and snapshot test
description: Adds support for the SOT-363 surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system, including a new component, integration into rendering logic, and tests for correctness.
body: This pull request adds support for the SOT-363 (also known as SOT457) surface-mount package to the 3D footprint rendering system. It introduces a new `SOT363` component, integrates it into the main rendering logic, and provides an example and a snapshot test for visual regression. **SOT-363 package support:** * Added new `SOT363` component in `lib/SOT-363.tsx` that defines the 3D model for the SOT-363 package, including chip body and leads. * Exported `SOT363` from the package index in `lib/index.ts` for public usage. * Registered `SOT363` in the main rendering logic in `lib/Footprinter3d.tsx`, allowing it to be rendered based on the `footprint` string. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R43) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-8ef5003688394a782da38d10f8dd9c9ece9af16db5a43ce66b655e6c19bb0bc9R198-R199) **Examples and testing:** * Added a usage example for SOT-363 in `examples/SOT-363.example.tsx`. * Added a snapshot test for the SOT-363 footprint in `tests/snapshots/sot363.test.ts` to ensure rendering correctness. ## 3D Render This render is correct the problem is in foorprinter, this pr fixes https://github.com/tscircuit/footprinter/pull/418 ## Ref https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/package-information/SOT363.pdf /fix #218
